    {
      "id": "7a2e2f5a0c912555f18e8019c8d8778ba8ad7b23",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-11-27 19:10:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nPer my previous comment, this isn't even fixed in upstream, so it could be needed for every distro. That said, it isn't clear to me whether this is just a warning that has no actual effect on the code, or if it is actually fixing a potential bug where some fields may be used without initialization.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a2929b079fca83a59582798e74a747e13e882486",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-11-27 19:22:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nLooking closely at that function, it appears that this is a false positive, in that the code is doing the right thing when ee_len = 0, but there are some accesses in ext4_zeroout_es() to fields that are not needed in this case.\n\nFor the upstream patch, there could also be a micro-optimization to ext4_zeroout_es() to move the ee_len check before ee_block and ee_pblock are set.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
